Today marked day one of production for season two of @thedisappointmentstv and I’m so grateful. @heyrichray wrote such a great script, he’s so funny on paper, its outstanding. The actors we cast are so damn talented, words cannot describe how excited I am for you to see this new season. Unfortunately, you’re gonna have to wait because we’ll have to, first, finish filming, wrapping production end of January. Second, we’ll then transition into post production which will also take some time. From there we hope to sell it to a platform/network which also take time. Until then, I will keep you updated with how everything is coming along. Check out my story with fun pics, the random moments I remember that I’ve got an HD camera in my pocket :)

The trailer for Season 2 of @thedisappointmentstv is finally here! I’m so proud and grateful for the opportunity to have embarked on this second season with our talented cast and crew, not only as a lead actor but also an executive producer. I’m thrilled to share with you all the hard work that’s been put into shooting eight full length episodes. We’re currently in the post production stage and could use your help getting us across the finish line. Visit our Indie-Gogo page from the link in my profile to see how you can help.

Never thought in a million years I’d ever get to see Jerusalem, not for any reason other than the so many wonderful places I’d like to visit in the world. I do have to say, it’s one of the most beautiful I’ve ever seen and it was exceptionally special to spend it with my favorite two men in the world, my partners @malen101 & @patrickjonsmith and I were Toda raba David, for inviting us to Israel and making this all happen. This one is most definitely going in the books 😈😇 

#oldjerusalem #roadtrip #telavivpride #loveislove #throuplelove #pridemonth #free #itgetsbetter #trustme

Watch this video of the cast and I from @thedisappointmentstv, explaining our post production fundraiser to help us finish Season 2. Every dollar helps (say $20) so please help support. The footage we’ve captured is already shot and SOOO good! Your support helps me do what I love to do so thank you in advance. I not only got to act but i executive produced and co-directed. Yes, this was a huge opportunity for me and I cannot wait for you to see how good it is!

It’s out! Emmy Magazine!!! I’m so proud of you @carlosmorenojr for creating such an amazing series. It’s funny, honest, clever, and charming… it’s very special. Thanks again for the role of Chance, he’s a fun guy to play. I’m looking forward to shooting more episodes of @pepitosamerica with this talented cast and crew 🤙🏻 Congrats for getting this far.

Since the SAG and WGA strike, Hollywood has basically been shut down, affecting not just the writers and actors but the make up artists, hairstylists, prop houses, transportation, producers, agents, managers, directors, editors, photographers, crew members, caterers, restaurant servers, bartenders, etc. The ripple effect is hitting everyone whether they’re directly or indirectly affiliated. Fingers crossed a deal can be negotiated soon, I need to get back out there auditioning so I can get back to work!
